Use **mxnet_predict-all.cc** is very convenient to make the model run in smart device. 

In my project (speech synthesis), I had used dnn to predict the output. But the input is with **variable length**.

 I had not found api for this type input, so I predict the output one by one... In fact, it is very slow.  The code is like this: 

```cpp
std::vector <std::vector<float>> DnnttsPredictor::process(std::vector <std::vector<float>> labData) {
        std::vector <std::vector<float>> outputs;
        for (int i = 0; i < labData.size(); i++) {
            std::vector<float> dnnOneInput = labData[i];
            MXPredSetInput(predictor_, "data", dnnOneInput.data(), dnnOneInput.size());
            MXPredForward(predictor_);
            mx_uint outputIndex = 0;
            std::vector<float> dnnOneOutput(outputDim_);
            MXPredGetOutput(predictor_, outputIndex, &(dnnOneOutput[0]), outputDim_);
            outputs.push_back(dnnOneOutput);
        }
        return outputs;
    }
```

